label: A7B6_hR13_166_ah_3c-001
title: Fe$_{7}$W$_{6}$ ($D8_{5}$) $\mu$-phase Structure
comments:
For more information on the $\mu$-phase, see (Pearson, 1972, p. 664). There it is referred to as a tetrahedrally close-packed Frank-Kasper structure. We have been unable to obtain a copy of the original reference for this structure (Arnfeldt, 1935), so we use the structure from (Villars, 1991, p.3415), which itself is taken from a secondary reference. 
 See \href{current_web_home_dir/A3B2C8_hR13_166_ac_c_ch-002}{the Ba$_{3}$Cr$_{2}$O$_{8}$ page} for ternary compounds with this structure. 
 Hexagonal settings of this structure can be obtained with the option {\tt --hex}.
